.Dd July 18, 1999
.Dt LINK 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm link
.Nd call the
.Fn link
function
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar file1
.Ar file2
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility performs the function call
.Fn link file1 file2 .
.Pp
.Ar file1
must be the pathname of an existing file, and
.Ar file2
is the pathname of the new link to
.Ar file1
to be created.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm
utility
exits 0 on success, and \*[Gt]0 if an error occurs.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr ln 1 ,
.Xr link 2 ,
.Xr unlink 8
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Nm
utility conforms to
.St -xcu5 .
